==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Globefish
<hw>Globe"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A plectognath fish of the genera <gen>Diodon</gen>,
<gen>Tetrodon</gen>, and allied genera. The globefishes can suck in
water or air and distend the body to a more or less globular form.
Called also <altname>porcupine fish</altname>, and <altname>sea
hedgehog</altname>. See <er>Diodon</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Globeflower</ent>⟦br⟧
